					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 120 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Perumānaḍigaḷ at Gōvindapāḍi in Valla-nāḍu a division of Dāmar-kōṭṭam, by <hi rend="bold">Pañchavaṉ-Mahādēviyār</hi>, who is stated to be the <hi rend="bold">consort of Śoḻapperumānaḍigal</hi> and to have <hi rend="bold">hailed from Kōṭṭūr in Neṉmali-nāḍu</hi> a division of Soḻa-nāḍu. Śōḻaperumānaḍigaḷ was evidently the reigning king, and the present record is one of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
